## 📋 **REPOSITORY SETUP INSTRUCTIONS**

### **1. Setup FruitfulGlobalPlanet Integration:**

```bash
# In codenest.git repository
cd codenest

# Add FruitfulGlobalPlanet as remote
git remote add planet https://github.com/Fruitful-global-planet/fruitfulPlanetChange.git

# Fetch metadata
git fetch planet

# Create integration branch
git checkout -b integrate-planet-metadata

# Pull specific metadata files
git checkout planet/main -- templates/
git checkout planet/main -- protocols/
git checkout planet/main -- subnodes/
git checkout planet/main -- styling/

# Commit integration
git add .
git commit -m "Integrate FruitfulGlobalPlanet metadata repository"
git push origin integrate-planet-metadata
```

### **2. Configure CodeNest to Pull from Planet:**

```javascript
// codenest/config.js
export const config = {
  planetRepo: {
    org: 'Fruitful-global-planet',
    repo: 'fruitfulPlanetChange',
    branch: 'main',
    paths: {
      templates: 'templates/',
      protocols: 'protocols/',
      subnodes: 'subnodes/',
      styling: 'styling/',
      treaties: 'treaties/'
    }
  },
  hotstack: {
    webhook: 'https://codenest.workers.dev/api/build',
    secret: process.env.HOTSTACK_SECRET
  },
  toynest: {
    activationEndpoint: 'https://toynest.faa.zone/api/activate',
    apiKey: process.env.TOYNEST_API_KEY
  }
};
```

### **3. Setup ToyNest Brand Activation:**

```bash
# In toynest.seedwave.git repository
cd toynest

# Configure wildcard subdomain routing
# Add to wrangler.toml:
routes = [
  { pattern = "*.toynest.faa.zone/*", zone_name = "faa.zone" }
]

# Deploy
wrangler deploy
```

### **4. Connect HotStack to CodeNest:**

```bash
# In hotstack.git repository
cd hotstack

# Add CodeNest webhook configuration
echo "CODENEST_WEBHOOK=https://codenest.workers.dev/api/build" >> .env
echo "CODENEST_SECRET=your_secret_here" >> .env

# Update upload handler to send to CodeNest
# See integration code above

# Deploy
wrangler deploy
```

